South Africa to Nominate Trevor Manuel to IMF, Emerging Markets Reports

-- B y   N a s r e e n   S e r i a
-- 
2011-06-10T08:16:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-10/south-africa-to-nominate-trevor-manuel-to-imf-emerging-markets-reports.html
South Africa  will nominate former
Finance Minister  Trevor Manuel  as a candidate to head the
 International Monetary Fund , Emerging Markets reported, citing
an unidentified government official.  Manuel has the backing of President  Jacob Zuma  and an
announcement is expected later today, which is the deadline for
nominations, the newspaper said on its website.  Zuma’s spokesman, Zizi Kodwa, didn’t immediately respond to
a text message seeking comment.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nasreen Seria at 
 nseria@bloomberg.net  